1.name: Captain Rex
1.description: Clone Captain Rex served the Republic during the Clone Wars, often taking orders from Anakin Skywalker and Ahsoka Tano

2.name: Fives
2.description: Also known as CT-27-5555, Fives trained with Domino Squad on Kamino before being shipped out to the Rishi Moon listening outpost.

3.name: Echo
3.description: Echo was a soldier in the Grand Army of the Republic, known for his strict adherence to orders and rules

4.name: Commander Cody
4.description: A natural and practical leader in the clone army, Cody was a good fit for General Kenobi, to whom he was particularly loyal.

5.name: Grand Moff Tarkin
5.description: As commander of the first Death Star, he proved to be the perfect blend of ruthless, calculating, and arrogant

6.name: Grand Admiral Thrawn
6.description: The blue-skinned Chiss was known for his love of art and strategy, and he used the latter to deconstruct his enemies.

7.name: Orson Krennic
7.description: Orson rose in the Imperial ranks along with the completion of the Death Star, until his unchecked ambition led to his reckoning on Scarif.

8.name: General Hux
8.description: Like most of his ilk, Armitage Hux is ruthless and cunning, and like Tarkin before him, he’s not afraid to stand up to his Force-wielding counterparts

9.name: Emperor Palpatine
9.description: Scheming, powerful, and evil to the core, Darth Sidious restored the Sith and destroyed the Jedi Order.

10.name: Kylo Ren
10.description: The son of Han Solo and Leia Organa, Ben Solo was seduced by the dark side of the Force and renamed himself Kylo Ren

11.name: Snoke
11.description: Snoke is powerful with the dark side of the Force, and seduced Ben Solo into abandoning the Jedi path to become his apprentice

12.name: Captain Phasma
12.description: she has no use for fancy titles or complex war rooms, preferring to lead her troops in battle against the First Order’s enemies
